{"questionId":"29618862","questionHtml":"<p>Find the product of the solutions of the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to form a cubic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for each of the terms <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>. Ignore extra terms.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>product of roots&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>product of roots of quadratic is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>product is therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29618862","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.10f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the product of the solutions of the equation fx=gx.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}